Sentencas: Layered perovskite oxide LaBa0.5Sr0.25Ca0.25Co2O5+delta (LBSCaCO) is studied as a potential cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOCFs).
Titulo: Characterization of layered double perovskite LaBa0.5Sr0.25Ca0.25Co2O5+δ as cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Ca-free sample LaBa0.5Sr0.25Co2O5+delta (LBSCO) is also investigated for comparison.
Titulo: Characterization of layered double perovskite LaBa0.5Sr0.25Ca0.25Co2O5+δ as cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The thermal expansion coefficient (TEC) value is reduced from 26.2 x 10(-6) K-1 to 20.0 x 10(-6) K-1 by Ca doping.
Titulo: Characterization of layered double perovskite LaBa0.5Sr0.25Ca0.25Co2O5+δ as cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity of LBSCaCO is above 500 S cm(-1) from room temperature to 800 degrees C. Substitution of Sr by Ca can effectively enhance the electrochemical performance.
Titulo: Characterization of layered double perovskite LaBa0.5Sr0.25Ca0.25Co2O5+δ as cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The area specific resistance (ASR) values of LBSCaCO and LBSCO are 0.075 Omega cm(2) and 0.084 Omega cm(2) at 800 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Characterization of layered double perovskite LaBa0.5Sr0.25Ca0.25Co2O5+δ as cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Moreover, LBSCaCO cathode achieves an excellent outputting of 662 mW cm(-2) at 800 degrees C. Based on these results, Ca doped layered perovskite LBSCaCO can be a cathode candidate material for IT-SOFC application.
Titulo: Characterization of layered double perovskite LaBa0.5Sr0.25Ca0.25Co2O5+δ as cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
